<BES xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="BES.xsd">
	<Fixlet>
		<Title>MS03-031: Cumulative Patch for Microsoft SQL Server / MSDE 2000 - Default MSSQLServer Instance on BES Server</Title>
		<Description><![CDATA[
<TABLE><TBODY><TR><TD> <P><FONT size=2>Microsoft has released a security bulletin outlining three newly discovered vulnerabilities in SQL Server 2000 Service Pack 3. The three vulnerabilities are: Named Pipe Hijacking, Named Pipe Denial of Service, and SQL Server Buffer Overrun. If exploited, these vulnerabilities can result in privilege elevation and can cause SQL Server to hang or cause arbitrary code to be executed on the machine. Microsoft has released the fix to these issues in the form of a cumulative patch. </FONT></P> <P><FONT face=Verdana size=2><STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>Important Note:</FONT></STRONG> Microsoft <STRONG>requires </STRONG>that all applications that are currently accessing the unpatched SQL server be closed in order for this patch to successfully apply. This includes the BES Console if the BES Console is running on a computer on which an unpatched SQL Server is present.</FONT></P> <P><FONT face=Verdana size=2><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> If this patch has already been installed on computers reporting relevant, it means that one or more files updated by the patch have been downgraded to unsafe versions. In order to ensure security, it is recommended that the patch be reinstalled.</FONT><BR><FONT face=Verdana size=2><BR><B>Note: </B>This Fixlet message detects and updates default MSSQLSERVER instances of SQL Server 2000.</FONT></P> <P><FONT face=Verdana size=2><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> Applying this patch to your BES Server will cause the SQL Server service on that computer to temporarily shut down.  The SQL Server service will restart when the application of this patch has completed.</FONT></P> <P><FONT size=2><FONT face=Verdana><STRONG>Note: </STRONG>Client machines will briefly display DOS windows while BES services stop and start again.</FONT></FONT></P> <P><FONT size=2><STRONG>Note:</STRONG> Microsoft has announced that this patch will be included in SQL Server 2000 Service Pack 4.</FONT></P> <P><FONT size=2><FONT face=Verdana><B>File Size: </B>14.3 MB</FONT></FONT></P> <P> </P><P><B>Note:</B> This Fixlet message does not have a default action. For more information on default actions, see BigFix KB #<a href="http://support.bigfix.com/cgi-bin/kbdirect.pl?id=474">474</a>.</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE>
]]></Description>
		<Relevance>(if( name of operating system starts with "Win" ) then platform id of operating system != 3 else false) AND (if exists property "in proxy agent context" then ( not in proxy agent context ) else true )</Relevance>
		<Relevance>(language of version block of file "kernel32.dll" of system folder contains "English") OR (exists value of key "HKLM\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\Nls\MUILanguages" of registry)</Relevance>
		<Relevance>not exists key "HKLM\Software\Wow6432Node\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion" whose (exists value "ProductId" of it OR exists value "CommonFilesDir" of it) of registry AND not exists values "PROCESSOR_ARCHITECTURE" whose (it as string as lowercase = "ia64") of keys "HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Session Manager\Environment" of registry</Relevance>
		<Relevance>exists key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Microsoft SQL Server" of registry</Relevance>
		<Relevance>exists key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Microsoft SQL Server" whose (value "InstalledInstances" of it as string as lowercase is "mssqlserver%00%00") of registry</Relevance>
		<Relevance><![CDATA[((value "SQLPath" of key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" of registry as string contains "%00") AND (version of file "sqlservr.exe" of folder "Binn" of folder (preceding text of last "%00" of (value "SQLPath" of key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" of registry as string)) >= "2000.80.760.0"  AND version of file "sqlservr.exe" of folder "Binn" of folder (preceding text of last "%00" of (value "SQLPath" of key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" of registry as string)) < "2000.80.818.0")) OR ((value "SQLPath" of key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" of registry as string does not contain "%00") AND (version of file "sqlservr.exe" of folder "Binn" of folder (value "SQLPath" of key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" of registry as string) >= "2000.80.760.0"  AND version of file "sqlservr.exe" of folder "Binn" of folder (value "SQLPath" of key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" of registry as string) < "2000.80.818.0"))]]></Relevance>
		<Relevance>(exists running service "BESGather") OR (exists running service "FillDB") OR (exists running service "GatherDB")</Relevance>
		<Relevance>((exists key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\MSSQLServer\Setup" whose (value "FeatureName" of it as string as lowercase is "sqlrun") of registry) OR (exists key "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Microsoft SQL Server\80\Registration" of registry))</Relevance>
